When you try to install Exchange 2007 mgmt tools on a machine running anything else than PowerShell V1 (yah yah I know, shouldn&rsquo;t run &ldquo;beta&rdquo; software in production, but I want my remoting).
So I guessed it was checking some registry value, did a bit of digging and found it it was looking for this :
&ldquo;HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PowerShell\1&rdquo; PID &ldquo;89383-100-0001260-04309&rdquo;
So using PowerShell&rsquo;s Set-item it looks something like this
Set-Item &ldquo;HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PowerShell\1&rdquo; PID &ldquo;89383-100-0001260-04309&rdquo;

$script:totalSize += ([System.Int64]$mailbox.Size)
