I am testing a new Syntax Highlighter to make made code posts look better&hellip;
The new one looks really good, and has some nice features like &ldquo;copy to clipboard&rdquo; and &ldquo;view plain&rdquo;, but unfortunately it does not support PowerShell&hellip;
So if you see my code snippets change appearance, you now know why :)

Imagine that you want to list, the last 15 events in all the eventlogs on the system, do you have to write several lines of codes to do that, like this below??
get-eventlog -logname Application -newest 15 get-eventlog -logname System -newest 15 get-eventlog -logname Application -newest 15
Of course not, PowerShell is much smarter than that&hellip;
You can use the &lsquo;foreach&rsquo; command.
foreach ($eventlog in (get-eventlog -list -asString)) {write-host $eventlog; get-eventlog $eventlog -newest 15}

